   &UR; INTERNATIONAL _ (Moved in ``i'' category)  &LR;
</P>
<P>
   NORWAY-TUNNEL (Hitra Island, Norway) _ Norwegians have long
looked out on their deep fjords, snow-crested peaks and scatterings
of scrub-covered islands as soaring symbols of their wilderness
culture. But shown that scene today, they are more likely to wonder
how they can scale over it, bore through it or burrow under it. The
breathtaking scenery that inspired Grieg's symphonies, Munch's
paintings and Ibsen's plays and poetry is now in thrall to the
creative instincts of Norway's plucky bridge and tunnel builders.
By Warren Hoge.
</P>
