analyst, advised investors to sell CUC shares. CUC's top executives
retaliated. They blackballed Renck, he says, refusing to return his
calls or answer his questions. Fast-forward to this April 15, when
Wall Street was stunned to learn that extensive ``accounting
irregularities'' had been uncovered at CUC, which by then had
merged with HFS Inc. to form Cendant Corp. By Diana B. Henriques.
