<P>
   LIFESTYLE
</P>
<P>
   BLIND _ Lori Hardy gave birth to her first child hoping, like
any other mother, for just a normal, healthy baby. She had no
reason to expect complications. But when Tyler Hardy was born three
years ago, doctors told her matter of factly that he had no eyes.
The Hardys were changed by the realization that their child would
not have a normal life, and that theirs would never be completely
normal again either. Through the Center for the Visually Impaired,
the couple, who live in Canton, are learning that blindness and
visual impairment are challenges to be met squarely, not shrunk
from. (Skube, Atlanta Journal-Constitution). 56. WITH PHOTOS.
</P>
