<P>
   GLASS-COLUMN _ WASHINGTON _ Internet guru Esther Dyson views her
virtual world as ``a source of untold productivity _ or a medium
for terrorists, con artists, and untrammeled lies and
viciousness.'' It's also a place that favors the technologically
elite _ savvy users with smooth access to cyberspace and other
nifty digital tools. In the real world, whether by dint of age,
class, education or race, many folks remain technologically
deprived. (Glass, Cox News Service) MOVED THURSDAY.
</P>
<P>
   TEEPEN-COLUMN _ Before he was president, I found myself on a
panel with Bill Clinton discussing the increasing intrusions into
the personal lives of politicians. Was the ventilation a good or a
bad thing or just, well, you know: a thing? I believe my exact
words were, ``Politicians should be whipped naked down the
street.'' I wish to change my testimony. (Teepen, Cox News Service)
MOVED THURSDAY.
</P>
<P>
   KLEINBERG-COLUMN _ MIAMI _ In recent days, a U.S. grand jury in
Puerto Rico indicted seven Cuban exiles on charges of plotting to
murder Fidel Castro. Thirty-eight years ago, John Kennedy and,
likely, his brother Bobby could have been indicted for the same
reason. (Kleinberg, Cox News Service) MOVED THURSDAY.
</P>
<P>
   BORDERS-COLUMN _ NACOGDOCHES, Texas _ I celebrated a birthday
recently. Send no presents, please. It's no big deal, though I am
now older than Elvis was when he died. Further, I do not believe
there are any active major-league baseball players older than me.
(Borders, Cox News Service) MOVED.
</P>
<P>
   NETHAWAY-COLUMN _ DINOSAUR VALLEY STATE PARK, Texas _ Watching
tourists track dinosaur tracks in the riverbed and along the banks
reminded me of the time my nephew and I came across fresh bear
tracks one summer high up in the Rocky Mountains. We followed the
large tracks for about an hour before it dawned on us that catching
up with the bear would be harmful to relatives who would fall down
laughing at our funeral. (Nethaway, Waco Tribune-Herald) MOVED.
</P>
<P>
   YOUNG-COLUMN _ Believe it or not, the best thing that's happened
to Ray and Frances lately has been for him to be declared
terminally ill. They are counting this among their blessings due to
new, ruthless Medicare rules. (Young, Waco Tribune-Herald) MOVED.
</P>
<P>
   HARMON-COLUMN _ GRAND JUNCTION, Colo. _ We've been so turned
upside down for so long that it's going to take us a while to get
our bearings in the brave new world of Clintonian sexual mores.
We're going to need new handbooks on office conduct and
expectations. (Harmon, Grand Junction Daily Sentinel) MOVED.
</P>
<P>
   KELSO-COLUMN _ AUSTIN, Texas _ With high school football upon
us, it's time to mention the need for Texas to eliminate the
superfluous letter A from the high school football size-ranking
system. (Kelso, Austin American-Statesman) MOVED.
</P>
