<SLUG> BC-BONNIE-FATALITY28-COX </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
&HT;   
</HEADLINE>
 &HT;    12-year-old child is only victim of Hurricane Bonnie in North
Carolina
 &HT;    Eds: ''Today'' is Friday.
 &HT;    By Emilio Sahurie
 &HT;    c. 1998 Cox News Service
<TEXT>
<P>
   BARCO, N.C. _ A 12-year-old girl, apparently the only North
Carolina victim of Hurricane Bonnie, died in her Barco home after a
tree crashed through her bedroom shortly after midnight Thursday
night.
</P>
<P>
   The large tree was toppled by heavy winds that reached up to 90
mph, said Currituck County Sheriff Glenn Brinkley.
</P>
<P>
   The incident occurred around midnight while the victim and her
family slept in their two-story home near Central Elementary
School. Brinkley said until all family members are notified of the
death, the name of the young girl will not be released.
</P>
<P>
   Because of power outages and road blocks due to fallen trees and
debris, members of the victim's family were forced to walk to the
Sheriff's Office in Currituck, several miles from the site of the
incident.
</P>
<P>
   After comforting the mother of the victim and a couple of her
children who were in shock, deputies and emergency crews responded
to the home of the victim. Working under generator-powered lights,
emergency personnel spent about an hour removing the large tree and
clearing debris to reach the body of the girl.
</P>
<P>
   The victim is one of two persons who have died as a result of
Hurricane Bonnie. A Myrtle Beach, S.C., man was electrocuted by a
generator he was working on when the storm passed the South
Carolina coast.
</P>
<P>
   Emilio Sahurie writes for The Daily Advance of Elizabeth City.
</P>
<P>
   Story Filed By Cox Newspapers
</P>
