<SLUG> BC-DIANA-ADVISORY-NYT </SLUG>
  
 Weekend editors, lifestyle editors, foreign editors:  
<TEXT>
<P>
   The New York Times plans one, and perhaps two, articles over the
weekend related to the anniversary of the death of Diana, the
Princess of Wales.
</P>
<P>
   The primary story will be:
</P>
<P>
   DIANA-ENGLAND (London) _ Moving on Sunday for Monday papers.
About Britain, the royals and the people a year after the fatal
crash. What are the lasting impacts, if any? How do people feel
now, as opposed to the convulsive grief of a year ago? What is the
reaction to the increasing commercialization surrounding her
memory? By Alan Cowell.
</P>
<P>
   A secondary, and tentative, story will be:
</P>
<P>
   DIANA-PARIS (Paris) _ Moving Saturday for Sunday papers, if
developments warrant: The scene at the site of the crash, and any
other news from the city where the princess died, as the
anniversary weekend commences. By Craig R. Whitney.
</P>
<P>
   &UR; The New York Times News Service  &LR;
</P>
</TEXT>
