<P>
   GORBACHEV ON YELTSIN'S `POLITICAL SUNSET.'
</P>
<P>
   -----------------------------------------
</P>
<P>
   A statement on the crisis in Russia by former Soviet leader
Mikhail Gorbachev has been sent from The New York Times Syndicate.
It is free to clients of the Gorbachev column and available for
purchase by non-clients.
</P>
<P>
   ``Today they (President Yeltsin and his entourage) seem to be
waking up to what's happening,'' writes the former leader of the
Soviet Union and Nobel Peace Prize winner. ``Continuing to cling to
power while closing their eyes and plugging their ears could be
self-defeating. The appointment of Chernomyrdin as acting prime
minister is therefore likely to signal the beginning of the process
of transferring power to an heir apparent. We are witnessing
Yeltsin's political sunset.''
</P>
<P>
   To see the complete article, which is titled ``There Is a Way
Out of the Russian Crisis,'' search in your system for the slug
BC-GORBACHEV-RUSSIAN-CRISIS-NYTSF. It has been sent to category
codes ``k'' and ``a.''
</P>
<P>
   For samples of Gorbachev's column on world affairs, call (888)
2-NYTSYN (888-269-8796), and you'll automatically be connected to a
New York Times Syndicate salesperson in your territory.
</P>
<P>
   Thank you.
</P>
<P>
   _ The New York Times Syndicate.
