<HEADLINE>
AT A GLANCE: 1998 LINCOLN NAVIGATOR
</HEADLINE>
 
(EDS: Accompanies CARS-WILLIAMS-COLUMN) (For use by NYTimes News Service clients) 
c.1998 Fort Worth Star-Telegram 
<TEXT>
<P>
   The Package: Full-size, five-door, seven- or eight-passenger,
V-8 powered, rear- or four- wheel-drive luxury sport-utility wagon,
an scale version of the Ford Expedition.
</P>
<P>
   Highlights: Roomy, powerful, lots of luxury features, quality
construction.
</P>
<P>
   Negatives: Standard bucket seats limit middle-row seating to two
persons; two-wheel-drive version slips and slides on wet roads.
</P>
<P>
   Major competitors: Ford Expedition, Chevrolet/GMC Suburban,
Range Rover, Toyota Land Cruiser/Lexus LX 470, Isuzu Trooper/Acura
SLX, Chevrolet Tahoe LS/GMC Yukon Denali.
</P>
<P>
   EPA fuel economy: 13 miles per gallon city, 17 highway.
</P>
<P>
   Base price: $39,310 plus $640 transportation.
</P>
<P>
   Price as tested: $40,800, including transportation.
</P>
<P>
   On The Road rating: A.
</P>
