<P>
   COLOMBIA-HEROIN (Pitayo, Colombia) _ Until recently, hundreds of
Paez Indians grew opium poppies and sold their narcotic-laden gum
to drug dealers. But the crimson blossoms became a curse. Pitayo
was plagued by shootings and public drunkenness. Alarmed tribal
elders decided that the flowers had to go. The initiative appears
to represent a rare victory in Colombia's war on drugs. By JOHN
OTIS.
</P>
<P>
   COLOMBIA-HEROIN-U.S. (Bogota, Colombia) _ Thirty years ago, the
infamous ``French Connection'' funneled heroin made from Turkish
opium in French laboratories to Italian crime families in New York.
These days, Colombia is the connection for many of the estimated 2
million heroin users in the United States. By JOHN OTIS.
</P>
