the Korean War, a memorial on the National Mall here was a long
time coming. It opened in 1995, 42 years after the bloody conflict
ended. Now, after only three years, it's crumbling because of
serious construction defects that will take a year and $2 million
to fix. By ERIC ROSENBERG. (Filed Thursday)
