glut, made worse by large supplies of pork and plenty of chicken.
People who invest in cattle feeding are taking a financial beating
said to be the worst since 1974. The slump is blamed, among other
things, on the Asian economic crisis and the Texas drought. By
NELSON ANTOSH.
