ECONOMIC CALENDAR: WEEK OF AUG. 31 
</HEADLINE>
   (For release Sunday, Aug. 30)  
 (bl)  
 c.1998 N.Y. Times News Service   
<TEXT>
<P>
   MONDAY
</P>
<P>
   The Agriculture Department reports on 1998 crop conditions for
wheat, corn, soybeans and cotton.
</P>
<P>
   The Commerce Department reports on new-home sales for July. A
decrease of 0.7 percent, to an annual rate of 928,000, is expected.
</P>
<P>
   TUESDAY
</P>
<P>
   The National Association of Purchasing Management releases the
purchasing managers' index for August. It is expected to rise 1.2
points, to 50.3.
</P>
<P>
   The Conference Board reports on the leading economic indicators
for July. They are expected to climb 0.2 percent over June.
</P>
<P>
   The Commerce Department discloses construction spending for
July. An increase of 0.8 percent is expected.
</P>
<P>
   Mitsubishi Bank-Schroder Wertheim releases its weekly index for
chain-store sales.
</P>
<P>
   LJR Redbook Research reports on retail sales.
</P>
<P>
   WEDNESDAY
</P>
<P>
   The Commerce Department reports on factory orders for July. A
gain of 0.2 percent from June is expected.
</P>
<P>
   THURSDAY
</P>
<P>
   The Labor Department releases weekly unemployment claims and
reports on joblessness for August. The unemployment rate is
expected to slip to 4.4 percent, from 4.5 percent in July.
</P>
<P>
   FRIDAY
</P>
<P>
   The Federal Reserve releases its weekly report on commercial and
industrial loans at banks.
</P>
