u s &Cx13;  &Cx11;  BC-HKN-BRUINS-BOS &LR;      08-28 0226
</HEADER>
<BODY>
<SLUG> BC-HKN-BRUINS-BOS </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
BRUINS SIGN RIGHT WING, DEFENSEMAN 
</HEADLINE>
   (For use by New York Times News Service clients)  
 By NANCY L. MARRAPESE  
 c.1998 The Boston Globe  
 
<TEXT>
<P>
   BOSTON _ The Bruins added some depth to their training camp
roster Friday, signing right wing Joel Trottier to a three-year
contract and defenseman Terry Virtue to a one-year deal.
</P>
<P>
   Trottier, 21, was taken by Boston in the seventh round of the
1997 entry draft and Virtue, 27, was an unrestricted free agent.
</P>
<P>
   Trottier played his final year of junior hockey in the Ontario
League last season. With Plymouth, he had 10 points in 10 games. He
was traded to Belleville and finished the season with 23 goals and
55 points in 43 games. In 10 postseason games, he had five goals
and 11 points.
</P>
<P>
   ``Trottier is an excellent prospect for us,'' said assistant
general manager Mike O'Connell. ``He's a terrific skater with an
offensive flair who had three 20-plus goal seasons, including one
40-goal season in four years of junior hockey.
</P>
<P>
   ``The signing of Virtue addresses our desire for more depth in
the organization, particularly on defense. He's been a solid
American League player for the past several seasons and he plays a
rugged, physical style.''
</P>
<P>
   Virtue, 27, who had 34 points and 233 penalty minutes in 74
games with Worcester, has been earmarked for Providence.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
