<P>
   RUSSIA-BANKAMERICA (Undated) _ The financial maelstrom ripping
through markets in Asia, Eastern Europe and Latin America added two
more banks to the growing casualty list of trading houses and
lenders swept into the storm's path. And while all eyes remain
focused on Russia's travails, it is now clearly apparent that
volatility in more economically significant countries like Brazil
and Argentina is eating into the profits of some financial concerns
doing business there. By Timothy L. O'Brien.
</P>
