<P>
   &QL; 
DISNEYHOAX (Undated) - The e-mail message seems too Goofy to be
true: Get a free trip to the Magic Kingdom just by clicking a
button. Computer users across the nation are receiving that
enticing promise, supposedly a reward for helping the Walt Disney
Co. check out a new computer program. And many of them bite. The
catch? The offer is as phony as the ears on a Mousketeer's hat. And
it's the latest in a series of e-mail hoaxes that spread like
wildfire, thanks to the ease electronic mail. By KATHLEEN INGLEY.
Story will move in the ``A`` category. &QL; 
 &QL; 
