<HEADLINE>
PURDUE DEFENSIVE END COULD SQUEEZE WELCH
</HEADLINE>
 (For use by NYTimes News Service clients) 
By SCOTT WOLF  
 c.1998 Los Angeles Daily News  
<TEXT>
<P>
   IRVINE _ One of the biggest concerns for USC on Sunday is how
sophomore offensive tackle Matt Welch matches up against Purdue
standout Chike Okeafor, a former All-Big Ten selection who was
suspended last season because of grade problems.
</P>
<P>
   USC doesn't have a lot of information on Okeafor, who hasn't
played since 1996 and has since changed positions.
</P>
<P>
   Okeafor, 6-foot-5 and 250 pounds, has been moved from linebacker
to defensive end and could pose problems for Welch, who has never
played in a Division I game and has sometimes struggled with his
pass blocking in practice.
</P>
<P>
   ``I'm just, you know, I need to concentrate a lot more,'' Welch
said. ``(I'm) a little nervous, I guess. I'm pretty prepared.''
</P>
<P>
   Welch won't be alone in his unfamiliarity. Four of USC's five
starting linemen have never started a college game.
</P>
<P>
   ``I think we're all pretty much in the same boat,'' Welch said.
</P>
<P>
   Big fan club: Sophomore linebacker Zeke Moreno expects to make
his first college start against Purdue, and his family is eagerly
awaiting it.
</P>
<P>
   Moreno has about 30 people attending the game, most of whom are
driving up from San Diego.
</P>
<P>
   ``It'll practically be a reunion,'' Moreno said. ``All my aunts
and uncles. I told them I would be starting.''
</P>
<P>
   Moreno is starting because senior Mark Cusano is recovering from
a pulled hamstring and his playing time could be limited.
</P>
<P>
   ``I'll be just as nervous as any game,'' Moreno said. ``But it's
gonna be great. Since last year, it's been hard for me not playing.
My mom's been telling me to be patient.''
</P>
<P>
   Another person who will watch the game is his brother Moses, a
three-year starter at quarterback for Colorado State who is now
playing for the Chicago Bears.
</P>
<P>
   McCutcheon rests: Cornerback Daylon McCutcheon did not practice
Friday because he was bothered by allergies, but he said he will
play Sunday.
</P>
<P>
   Larry's fine: Defensive end Lawrence Larry of Littlerock
proclaimed his sore ankle fit on Friday and said he will be able to
play. Hackett has not decided if he will start Larry or freshman
Ryan Nielsen from Royal High.
</P>
<P>
   Anniversaries: This season marks several notable anniversaries
for USC football. It's the 20th anniversary of the last national
championship team, the 70th anniversary of its first championship
team, and the 75th anniversary of the first USC football game at
the Coliseum.
</P>
<P>
   Camp's over: USC officially broke camp in Irvine on Friday and
returned to Los Angeles. The Trojans will practice this morning at
the Coliseum while Purdue holds it workout this afternoon. Both are
closed to the public.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
