<HEADLINE>
&HT;   
</HEADLINE>
 &HT;    CLINTON RUSSIA, IRELAND SCHEDULE
 &HT;    With CLINTON-TRIP-$ADV30.
 &HT;    For Use Sunday, Aug. 30 And Thereafter.
 &HT;    By BOB DEANS 
 &HT;    c.1998 Cox News Service 
<TEXT>
<P>
   WASHINGTON _ On Monday, President Clinton leaves for a five-day
trip to Russia, Northern Ireland and the Republic of Ireland.
Following is an overview of his schedule:
</P>
<P>
   Tuesday, Sept. 1 -- In Moscow for first day of summit meeting
with President Boris Yeltsin.
</P>
<P>
   Wednesday, Sept. 2 -- In Moscow for second day of summit meeting
with Yeltsin; meeting with Russian parliamentary and political
party leaders.
</P>
<P>
   Thursday, Sept. 3 -- In Belfast for meeting with Northern
Ireland Assembly; visiting victims of latest bombing in Armagh.
</P>
<P>
   Friday, Sept. 4 -- In Dublin for meeting Bertie Ahern, prime
minister if the Republic of Ireland; speech on the Irish peace
process.
</P>
<P>
   Saturday, Sept. 5 -- In Limerick, Ireland, for a speech;
afternoon of golf; returns to Washington in the evening.
</P>
<P>
   ENDIT
</P>
<P>
   Story Filed By Cox Newspapers
</P>
<P>
   For Use By Clients of the New York Times News Service
</P>
