<HEADLINE>
&HT;   
</HEADLINE>
 &HT;    On Deck: ST. LOUIS CARDINALS
 &HT;    By Thomas Stinson
 &HT;    c. 1998 Cox News Service
<TEXT>
<P>
   When: 1:15 p.m.
</P>
<P>
   Where: Busch Stadium.
</P>
<P>
   TV/radio: WAGA (Channel 5); 750-AM.
</P>
<P>
   Probable starting pitchers: LHP Tom Glavine (17-5, 2.57; 11-4,
3.73 lifetime vs. Cardinals) vs. RHP Kent Bottenfield (4-5, 4.51;
1-1, 1.80 lifetime vs. Braves).
</P>
<P>
   Notes: Glavine's 17 victories already surpass any of his four
previous seasons. He is destined for his first 20-victory campaign
since going 22-6 in 1993, his career best. With at least four,
perhaps five, more starts this season, he might match it. Glavine
is coming off a 4-3 victory over Los Angeles, when he gave up 10
hits, resigned himself to a loss and then watched the Braves score
four in the eighth off Jeff Shaw. He is 5-2 in the second half, but
has given up only 13 runs in his last 60 innings (1.95 ERA) thanks
mainly to back-to-back shutouts Aug. 7 against San Francisco and
Aug. 13 against San Diego. Bottenfield, released by the Cubs last
winter, made the Cardinals as a middle reliever but joined the
rotation on June 15, when Donovan Osborne, who has since returned
to action, was sidelined. Bottenfield is 3-3 as a starter with a
4.09 ERA. It will be his 15th start. In previous stints with
Montreal, Colorado, San Francisco and Chicago, he started a total
of 30 games, going 6-11 with a 5.04 ERA. He drew no decision in an
Aug. 1 game at Turner Field, throwing seven shutout innings before
the Braves scored three time off Rich Croushore in the eighth to
win 3-1.
</P>
<P>
   Story Filed By Cox Newspapers
</P>
